# Title: Uncommon Child Process Of Conhost.EXE
# Author: omkar72
# Date: 2020-10-25
# Level: medium
# Description: Detects uncommon "conhost" child processes. This could be a sign of "conhost" usage as a LOLBIN or potential process injection activity.
# MITRE Tactic: Defense Evasion
# Tags: attack.defense-evasion, attack.t1202
# Reference: https://github.com/SigmaHQ/sigma/blob/master/rules/windows/process_creation/proc_creation_win_conhost_susp_child_process.yml

ParentImage="*\\conhost.exe" NOT (Image="*:\\Windows\\System32\\conhost.exe" OR Image="" OR NOT Image=*) NOT Provider_Name="SystemTraceProvider-Process"